init_account.doc:
Create a new DCA account with current GlobalConfig settings.
 start_time_ms: Optional start time in milliseconds. Pass 0 to start immediately (default).
                If non-zero, the first trade can only execute after this time + interval.

new.doc:
Create a new DCA account.
 start_time_ms: Optional start time in milliseconds. Pass 0 to start immediately (default).
                If non-zero, the first trade can only execute after this time + interval.

init_trade.doc:
Initialize a trade. Restricted to friend modules (whitelisted adapters) for security.
 This prevents malicious executors from stealing user funds by not completing swaps.
 Caller gets executor reward as incentive. Fee is deducted and sent to treasury.

resolve_trade.doc:
Resolve a trade. Called after swap completes.
 Restricted to friend modules (whitelisted adapters) for security.
 executor_reward is validated against the snapshotted budget to prevent theft.
 output_amount is the actual amount received from the DEX (for event tracking).

effective_slippage_bps.doc: Get effective slippage: custom if set, otherwise default from config

interval_to_seconds.doc: Convert every + time_scale to seconds for interval validation

set_delegatee.doc: Owner can change the delegatee address

set_slippage.doc:
Owner can set custom slippage tolerance (overrides default)
 Slippage must be within protocol's max_slippage_bps limit

reset_slippage.doc: Owner can reset slippage to use default from config

set_inactive.doc: Owner can pause their DCA account at any time

reactivate_as_owner.doc: Owner can reactivate their DCA account if it has funds and remaining orders

redeem_funds_and_deactivate.doc: Owner can withdraw all funds and deactivate - effectively canceling the DCA

withdraw_input.doc: Owner can partially withdraw input funds (reducing remaining orders proportionally)

add_executor_reward.doc: Owner can add more executor reward balance to the account

slippage_bps.doc: Custom slippage tolerance in basis points (overrides default if set)

DCACreatedEvent.doc: Emitted when a new DCA account is created

total_orders.doc: Total number of orders to execute

fee_bps.doc: Fee rate in basis points (snapshotted at creation)

executor_reward_per_trade.doc: Executor reward per trade in MIST (snapshotted at creation)

default_slippage_bps.doc: Default slippage tolerance in basis points

TradeInitiatedEvent.doc: Emitted when init_trade is called (trade initiated)

executor.doc: Address that triggered the trade (for keeper tracking)

input_amount.doc: Input amount sent to DEX (after fee deduction)

fee_amount.doc: Fee amount deducted and sent to treasury

active.doc: Whether the DCA account is still active

DCADeactivatedEvent.doc: Emitted when a DCA account is deactivated

SlippageUpdatedEvent.doc: Emitted when slippage tolerance is updated
